params._depositManager: The address of the DepositManager contract.
params._layer2Address: The address of the Layer 2 contract.
params._name: The name of the ERC20 token.
params._seigManager: The address of the SeigManager contract.
params._symbol: The symbol of the ERC20 token.

returns._0: The address of the newly created WSTON token proxy.

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

params._l1ton: The address of the L1 TON token.
params._l1wton: The address of the L1 WTON token.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

params._imp: The address of the new implementation contract.

params.newImplementation: The address of the new implementation contract.
params.wstonProxyAddress: The address of the WSTON token proxy to upgrade.

createWSTONToken(address,address,address.notice: Creates a new WSTON token proxy and initializes it. Only the factory owner or admins ar authorized to call this function.the function caller becomes the contract owner and is able to upgrade it through the upgradeWstonTo function

initialize(address,address).notice: Initializes the factory contract with the given WTON and TON addresses.

setWstonImplementation(address).notice: Sets the implementation address for WSTON tokens.

upgradeWstonTo(address,address).notice: Upgrades the WSTON token proxy to a new implementation.
